news.title: Over 3.36 lakh families in Kerala own land but have no houses
news.para: This number is likely to vary as the reverification of applications is underway to publish the final list by April 30. Government had received as many as 9,20,260 applications for houses under Life Mission since July 1, 2020.

news.title: Gurugram: Handover of colonies by May 31, DLF wants upkeep fees cleared
news.para: The decision to extend the takeover deadline was taken at a meeting on Wednesday, which was chaired by MCG commissioner Mukesh Kumar Ahuja and attended by DLF representatives.

news.title: Rustomjee Group to set up realty investment platform, raise over Rs 570 crore
news.para: The proposed investment and development platform will focus on real estate projects in Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR) mainly in residential and mixed-use developments. Going forward, the platform will also invest in completed mixed-use commercial assets across key cities of the country.

news.title: Government to form committee to study, offer resolutions to stalled housing projects
news.para: The committee will provide a resolution and propose a future course of action to ensure that homebuyers get delivery of their homes in these stalled projects, the Ministry of Housing & Urban Affairs (MoHUA) said.

news.title: Rs 702 crore MahaRERA recovery warrants yet to be executed in Maharashtra
news.para: Latest statistics available with the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) revealed that such warrants have been issued to developers of 271 projects across the state. Of these, 83 are in Pune, followed by 66 in Mumbai suburban and 50 in Thane.

news.title: Non-execution of 2,600 MahaRERA orders in four years miffs buyers in Maharashtra
news.para: Some of the customers said in cases where the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) had issued orders in their favour, they had to repeatedly follow up with the developers and ultimately file the non-compliance applications.

news.title: Sebi to auction 15 properties on May 11 to recover investors' money
news.para: Out of the 15 properties, nine belong to Sun Plant Business, four relate to Sun Plant Agro and the remaining two belong to Remac Realty.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate raises Rs 865 crore
news.para: In a regulatory filing, IBREL said that the fund raising committee of the board of directors, at its meeting held on April 12, approved the issue and allotment of 8,55,59,435 equity shares to qualified institutional buyers at an issue price of Rs 101.10 per share, aggregating to a little over Rs 865 crore.

news.title: UK's housebuilders commit $6.5 billion to fix cladding
news.para: UK Housing Secretary Michael Gove has used a carrot-and-stick approach to tackle the issue, forcing housebuilders including top London-listed firms to sign up for the safety pledge, mainly on cladding repair works.

news.title: iSprout takes three lakh sq ft space in Hyderabad & Bengaluru
news.para: iSprout is undertaking properties sized 1 lakh sq ft in Divyashree Trinity and 90,000 sq ft in My Home Twitza, Hyderabad. In Bengaluru, it is undertaking 1 lakh sq ft in Shilpitha Tech Park.

news.title: Ashiana Housing sales bookings up 7% to Rs 573.25 crore in FY22
news.para: The company sold 14.76 lakh square ft in FY22 as against 14.97 lakh square ft in the preceding fiscal. "1,051 units were booked in FY22 vis-a-vis 1,131 units booked in FY21," the filing said.

news.title: CHS's NOC not needed to sell, rent flats, says Maharashtra housing minister
news.para: State housing minister Jitendra Awhad, who is the NCP MLA from Mumbra, said all that a flat owner needs from a housing society at the time of selling a flat is a no dues pending certificate.

news.title: Prestige Estates sales bookings up 90% to record Rs 10,382 crore in FY22
news.para: The sales bookings of Bengaluru-based Prestige Estates came in higher than Macrotech Developers, which markets its properties under the Lodha brand. Macrotech reported 51 per cent growth in its sales booking to a record Rs 9,024 crore during the last fiscal.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh HC issues notices over regularization of illegal construction
news.para: The petitioner has alleged that entire state of Himachal Pradesh is in danger on account of erratic, irrational and uncontrolled construction of housing and commercial complexes. The respondents have been directed to file reply and the matter has been fixed for May 9.

news.title: Panchkula civic body to hold camps to resolve tax issues
news.para: Officials said that on April 13, a special camp for residents living in Sector 15 and nearby areas would be held at Jain Bhawan in Sector 15 from 9am to 4pm.
